                }
              ]
            },
            "valueString": "61-year-old male with 18-month history of progressive low back pain and bilateral lower extremity claudication. MRI shows moderate central canal stenosis at L4-L5 with Grade I degenerative spondylolisthesis. EMG/NCV shows mild bilateral L5 radiculopathy. Patient has type 2 diabetes (most recent A1C 8.2%), BMI 34."
          },
          {
            "sequence": 2,
            "category": {
              "coding": [
                {
                  "system": "http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/claiminformationcategory",
                  "code": "info",
                  "display": "Information"
                }
              ]
            },
            "valueString": "Conservative treatment: Physical therapy x 8 sessions over 6 weeks — some improvement in function. One lumbar epidural steroid injection (L4-L5) with 40% pain relief lasting 3 weeks. No second ESI attempted. Patient reports pain 6/10 at rest, 8/10 with ambulation > 2 blocks. Currently on gabapentin 300mg TID and meloxicam 15mg daily."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
